claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: Title page header of an original article titled "Recombinant or Standard-Dose Influenza Vaccine in Adults under 65 Years of Age" with author names listed, but no dosing information visible. The image only shows the article title and authors and does not provide any details on HA micrograms per strain in Flublok or standard-dose vaccines, so it does not support the claim.
